    "narrative": "Today\u2019s rotation for LawDog reflects a cautious approach against a relatively tough slate of opposing starters. **Gleyber Torres** (Score: 51.30) stands as our most reliable offensive engine; while facing Abel, **Gleyber Torres** benefits from a high-leverage spot in the #2 hole and a park factor boost that helps offset the efficiency dip from his platoon splits against right-handed pitching. **Gavin Sheets** (Score: 45.53) holds onto a starting spot despite a middling matchup against Herget, largely driven by the dynamic platoon advantage afforded by the right-handed opposing arm, though his lower position in the order keeps his ceiling capped. **Geraldo Perdomo** (Score: 41.97) remains in the lineup due to his premium batting order position, but he faces significant resistance today against McLean; the SP skill of the opposing pitcher drags his output down by nearly 20%, making him a marginal play as we chase stability over raw power.\n\nThe benching of **Lawrence Butler** was the most difficult decision of the cycle. While **Lawrence Butler** possesses the high-speed upside we covet for the SB category, the combination of a left-on-left matchup against Weathers and his exclusion from the primary starting lineup necessitated an immediate benching to preserve our limited game caps. We are currently navigating a quiet day for the core of our roster, as **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez**, **Cal Raleigh**, and **Will Smith** are all unavailable due to scheduled off-days. With elite assets like **Luis Arraez**, **Masyn Winn**, and **Jung Hoo Lee** waiting in the wings for future matchups, we are prioritizing volume control today. Monitor the weather reports near the venue for **Gavin Sheets**, as any sudden shifts in wind could further depress his already marginal efficiency score.",
